structured.title: Friends Chat About Golf And Stargazing
structured.overview: The conversation is a casual morning chat between the user and someone named Exactly. They talk about the wet weather, which has caused the local golf course to close due to flooding and concerns about damaging the turf. Exactly mentions having only played golf twice since November because of the rain. The user then talks enthusiastically about a proper telescope they received, which can see planets. They describe having briefly viewed Jupiter and three of its moons from their garden, but continued cloud cover has largely prevented further use. They also reference a one‚Äëhour viewing window at the Cardiff museum area, near the old RAF base. No concrete plans or commitments are made; it‚Äôs mainly sharing updates and frustrations about weather affecting their hobbies.

apps_results.content:
## Weather and golf conditions
- Heavy rain caused flooding on golf course  
- Course closed today and tomorrow to prevent turf damage  
- Playing on wet ground slows course recovery  

## Golf playing context
- One person has only played twice since November  
- Wet winter weather limited golf opportunities  

## Family and travel mention
- Parents went to Australia on January 4, 2026  
- Since then, it has rained almost every day  

## Telescope and astronomy
- User received a proper telescope for birthday in January  
- First use: saw Jupiter and three moons  
- Since then, nightly cloud cover blocked further viewing  

## Location details
- User mentioned a one-hour viewing window in Cardiff museum  
- Museum located behind the old RAF base  

## Next steps
- Wait for clear skies to use telescope again  
- Resume golf when course reopens and ground dries
